startsWithB

private boolean startsWithB(String bType,
                            String iType)
Determines if the read type is the same as the current type with the only difference being that the current type (bType) starts with "B-" and the read type starts with "I-".

Parameters:
bType - - the current type for the chunk or named entity
iType - - the read chunk or named entity type for the token being examined.
Returns:
true if we should consder iType to be the same as bType so we know not to make a new chunk or named entity.
